<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1438,474,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,318,698,724]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Tergite 7 of male with medial and posterolateral projections; male terminalia with the gonostyle forming an acute, heavily sclerotized process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1438,474,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,773,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Description.</emphasis>
Male. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[435,505,773,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Color</emphasis>
. General body coloration brown. Length, ca. 
<quantity box="[1046,1140,773,799]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1219,773,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Head</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1335,773,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[170,1416,174,1965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male. A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view. C. Antennal flagellomere 8, lateral view. D. Palpus, lateral view. E. Wing, dorsal view. F. Haltere, lateral view. Scale (mm): A, C, D (0.04), B(0.064), E (0.42), F(0.16)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301746/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) brown, length 
<quantity box="[232,337,810,836]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
in lateral view, eyes pubescent. Labella setose. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1119,810,836]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[170,1416,174,1965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male. A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view. C. Antennal flagellomere 8, lateral view. D. Palpus, lateral view. E. Wing, dorsal view. F. Haltere, lateral view. Scale (mm): A, C, D (0.04), B(0.064), E (0.42), F(0.16)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301746/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) brown, 
<quantity box="[1227,1332,810,836]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.41">0.41 mm</quantity>
long, 10 brown flagellomeres, covered by sparse minute, hair-like microtrichia; flagellomeres 1–9 with a whorl of 
<emphasis box="[151,346,885,910]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">sensilla chaetica</emphasis>
on the medial portion and with distinct 
<typeStatus box="[814,864,885,911]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
distal antennal sensilla on posterior margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[170,1416,174,1965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male. A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view. C. Antennal flagellomere 8, lateral view. D. Palpus, lateral view. E. Wing, dorsal view. F. Haltere, lateral view. Scale (mm): A, C, D (0.04), B(0.064), E (0.42), F(0.16)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301746/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); flagellum length, 
<quantity box="[426,535,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.33">0.33 mm</quantity>
, last flagellomere club-shape, 
<quantity box="[904,1010,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
long, sparsely setose and abundant scattered antennal sensillae above basal whorl of setae. Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[955,1051,960,986]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[170,1416,174,1965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male. A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view. C. Antennal flagellomere 8, lateral view. D. Palpus, lateral view. E. Wing, dorsal view. F. Haltere, lateral view. Scale (mm): A, C, D (0.04), B(0.064), E (0.42), F(0.16)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301746/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
) brown, length 
<quantity box="[1254,1367,960,986]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.06">0.06 mm</quantity>
, with sparsely setae and palpal sensillae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[595,699,997,1023]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Thorax.</emphasis>
Reddish brown, scutum with sparsely covered short setae; scutellum with scattered setae; anterior spiracular sclerite with 30–32 setae, supra-alar setae, 5–6; antepronotum, proepimeron and proepisternum with scattered setae; anepisternum with 4 anterior setae, last setae stronger and longer than remaining setae; katepisternum and meron bare. Wing. (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1276,1109,1135]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[170,1416,174,1965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male. A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view. C. Antennal flagellomere 8, lateral view. D. Palpus, lateral view. E. Wing, dorsal view. F. Haltere, lateral view. Scale (mm): A, C, D (0.04), B(0.064), E (0.42), F(0.16)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301746/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
) length, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.58" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="1.58">1.58 mm</quantity>
; width, 
<quantity box="[308,408,1146,1172]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
. R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[444,452,1162,1176]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">1</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[538,565,1162,1176]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">4+5</subScript>
with irregularly arranged rows of short setae on dorsal surface; Sc incomplete, with 3–4 pores; base of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[604,612,1203,1217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">1</subScript>
largely absent; macrotrichia present on veins M 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1180,1188,1203,1217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1228,1236,1203,1217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">2</subScript>
, CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1307,1315,1203,1217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1428,1436,1203,1217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">2</subScript>
and some along the wing margin in the apical region and posterior margin, including anal region. Halter (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[182,1403,184,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[170,1416,174,1965]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male. A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view. C. Antennal flagellomere 8, lateral view. D. Palpus, lateral view. E. Wing, dorsal view. F. Haltere, lateral view. Scale (mm): A, C, D (0.04), B(0.064), E (0.42), F(0.16)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301746/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
) brown, covered with fine micropilosity on entire surface, with three lateral setae and three apical setae on knob. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[305,439,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[164,1431,207,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-69@4.[151,1436,194,1790]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male legs, lateral view, A. anterior, B. middle. C. hind, D. hind leg, tarsomere I. Scale (mm): A–C (0.16), D (0.04)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301748/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 2A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[453,491,1302,1328]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,202,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-59@6.[149,1440,194,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, B), (C, D paratype female). A. hind leg, tarsomere I, lateral view. B. Sternite 6 posterior margin, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. Without scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">4A</figureCitation>
) brown, with pigmentation pattern. Coxae brown; front and mid femora pale brown, hind femur with narrow basal and distal reddish brown rings. Tibiae with basal reddish brown rings. Tarsi brown. Femora and tibiae with scattered setae, all tibiae with posteroapical spine-like setae and tibial comb in a regular row. Tarsomeres I armed with stout ventral spines in a palisade row (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1289,1414,1440]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[164,1431,207,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-69@4.[151,1436,194,1790]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male legs, lateral view, A. anterior, B. middle. C. hind, D. hind leg, tarsomere I. Scale (mm): A–C (0.16), D (0.04)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301748/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1303,1343,1414,1440]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,202,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-59@6.[149,1440,194,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, B), (C, D paratype female). A. hind leg, tarsomere I, lateral view. B. Sternite 6 posterior margin, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. Without scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">4A</figureCitation>
); apical spine-like setae present on fore tarsomeres I, mid tarsomeres I–II, hind tarsomeres I–III. Claws strongly curved; empodia present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1438,474,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">
Abdomen dark brown. Tergite 1 with microreticulation. Sternite 6 (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1132,1526,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,202,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-59@6.[149,1440,194,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, B), (C, D paratype female). A. hind leg, tarsomere I, lateral view. B. Sternite 6 posterior margin, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. Without scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) with a medial group of spinose setae at posterior margin; tergite 7 with posteromedial and lateral projections (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1234,1328,1563,1589]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1417,211,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-65@5.[151,1436,194,1897]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, C, D), (B paratype). A. Male. B. Female. Dorsal view, tergite 7 (above), sternite 7 (below). C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale (mm): A–B (0.16), C– D (0.064)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), sternite 7 (
<figureCitation box="[183,276,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1417,211,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-65@5.[151,1436,194,1897]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, C, D), (B paratype). A. Male. B. Female. Dorsal view, tergite 7 (above), sternite 7 (below). C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale (mm): A–B (0.16), C– D (0.064)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) concave posteriorly, with posterior margin heavily sclerotized. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1043,1181,1600,1626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1198,1338,1600,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1417,211,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-65@5.[151,1436,194,1897]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, C, D), (B paratype). A. Male. B. Female. Dorsal view, tergite 7 (above), sternite 7 (below). C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale (mm): A–B (0.16), C– D (0.064)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Figs. 3C–D</figureCitation>
) length, 
<quantity box="[151,259,1638,1664]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.33">0.33 mm</quantity>
, width, 
<quantity box="[354,462,1638,1664]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.18">0.18 mm</quantity>
; strongly sclerotized basal, claw-shaped projection; male terminalia with an acute, heavily sclerotized medial gonostyle; epandrium fused to the gonocoxites, with pair of adjacent setose lobes; aedeagus C-shaped in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1438,474,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">
Female. Differing from male as follows. Antenna brown, 
<quantity box="[873,977,1750,1776]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
long. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1052,1151,1749,1775]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Thorax.</emphasis>
Anepisternum with 5–7 anterior setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[330,407,1786,1812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Wing.</emphasis>
Length, 
<quantity box="[518,629,1787,1813]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.79" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="1.79">1.79 mm</quantity>
; width, 
<quantity box="[727,839,1787,1813]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.76">0.76 mm</quantity>
. Abdomen with tergite 7 as in 
<figureCitation box="[1215,1309,1787,1813]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1417,211,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-65@5.[151,1436,194,1897]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, C, D), (B paratype). A. Male. B. Female. Dorsal view, tergite 7 (above), sternite 7 (below). C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale (mm): A–B (0.16), C– D (0.064)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
; sternite 7 concave (
<figureCitation box="[264,358,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1417,211,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-65@5.[151,1436,194,1897]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, C, D), (B paratype). A. Male. B. Female. Dorsal view, tergite 7 (above), sternite 7 (below). C. Terminalia, ventral view. D. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale (mm): A–B (0.16), C– D (0.064)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[580,721,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,202,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-59@6.[149,1440,194,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, B), (C, D paratype female). A. hind leg, tarsomere I, lateral view. B. Sternite 6 posterior margin, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. Without scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Figs. 4C–D</figureCitation>
; tergite 8 triangular, with a pair of basal spiracles (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1422,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,202,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-59@6.[149,1440,194,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Thripomorpha ungula n. sp. (holotype): Male (A, B), (C, D paratype female). A. hind leg, tarsomere I, lateral view. B. Sternite 6 posterior margin, dorsal view. C. Terminalia, dorsal view. D. Terminalia, ventral view. Without scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301752/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); sternite 8 surface with membranous aspect, posteriorly rounded, with a deep median cleft; vaginal furca rounded anteriorly, well sclerotized. Spermatheca oval, sclerotized; length, including neck, 
<quantity box="[1222,1330,1899,1925]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
